b"[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](av103.htm)  [Next](av105.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n## VI, 82. Charm for obtaining a wife.\n\n1\\. I call the name of him that comes here, that hath come here, and is\narriving; I crave (the name) of Indra, Vritra's slayer, the Visava, of\nhundredfold strength.  \n2\\. The road by which the Asvins carried away as a bride Surya, Savitar's\ndaughter,'by that road,' Bhaga (fortune) told me, 'thou shalt bring here a\nwife'!  \nWith thy wealth-procuring, great, golden hook, O Indra, husband of Saki,\nprocure a wife for me that desireth a wife!\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: VI, 78. Blessing for a married couple](av105.htm)\n\n"